<item>
            <title>[LU-9256] lfs setstripe/getstripe support negative flags</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9256</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;lfs setstripe&quot; doesn&apos;t support negative flags, which make it not convenient for user to delete all non-instantiated components by a single command. We should make &apos;lfs setstripe/getstripe&quot; to support negative flag like &quot;^init&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;lfs find&quot; already uses &apos;!&apos; for excluding match, it&apos;s not necessary to introduce negative flags for it to make thing complicated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
